Ministry of Public Health reported [Thu 17 Dec 2020] that out of 1647 samples, 232 cases have turned positive in the last 24 hours.

At least 176 358 people have so far been tested in the governmental labs, and there still are 8848 known active cases in the country.

According to the ministry, within 24 hours, 38 individuals have recovered from COVID-19, and 15 individuals are reported dead.

The total number of cases in Afghanistan is 50 202, total deaths are 2032 and the total recoveries are recorded at 38 686.

