[C] India
Date: Fri 18 Dec 2020 06:17 IST
Source: The Times of India, Times News Network (TNN) [edited]
https://timesofindia.indiatimes.com/india/slide-in-daily-covid-count-continues-india-inches-closer-to-1-crore-cases/articleshow/79788466.cms


The downslide in COVID-19 cases across the states continued even as India inched closer to the mark of one crore [10 million] total cases on [Thu 17 Dec 2020], with 26 691 fresh infections taking the country's caseload to 9 977 775.

Fresh infections were lower by nearly 2000 from the [Wed 16 Dec 2020] tally of 28 465 and by nearly 3000 cases compared to last [Thu 17 Dec 2020].

The decline was seen in fatalities, too, as 334 deaths were reported on [Thu 17 Dec 2020] compared to 357 the previous day.

Casualties this week have remained below 400 on all days so far, in contrast to last week, when they crossed the 400-mark on 4 days. India's cumulative toll reached 144 781 on [Thu 17 Dec 2020].

The slide in active cases continued for the 20th consecutive day, and the tally now stands at 313 127. However, compared to [Wed 16 Dec 2020], when active cases had dropped by more than 15 000, the decline in these cases was by less than 5000 on [Thu 17 Dec 2020]. The number of patients cured by the virus has reached 9 519 867, reflecting a recovery rate of 95.4%.

Kerala retained the top position among the states in fresh infections, with 4969 patients testing positive, followed by Maharashtra (3880 new cases), West Bengal (2245), Chhattisgarh (1584), and Uttar Pradesh (1539). Delhi, which had seen a huge surge in infections a few weeks ago, was at the 6th place with 1363 new cases. However, in fatalities, Delhi was at the 3rd spot with 35 fresh deaths, after Maharashtra (65) and West Bengal (44).

