Source: The Himalayan Times [edited]
https://thehimalayantimes.com/nepal/nepal-covid-19-update-736-new-cases-847-recoveries-13-fatalities-recorded-today/


Nepal's Health Ministry, in its regular press briefing, shared the latest updates on the coronavirus contagion from across the country and government's response to the health crisis.

Till date [16 Dec 2020], 1 849 136 tests through polymerase chain reaction (PCR) testing have been carried out, wherein 5555 tests were performed in the last 24 hours.

At present, there are 452 people under quarantine in various facilities across the country. The number of active cases in Nepal is 9757.

736 new cases of the coronavirus infection were registered today [16 Dec 2020] taking the national tally to 250 916.

As many as 847 persons earlier diagnosed with the disease have tested negative in the last 24 hours. With the recent addition, the national COVID-19 recovery tally has now reached 239 416.

Meanwhile, 13 more fatalities were confirmed by the Ministry today [16 Dec 2020], with which the country's COVID-19 death tally has now reached 1743.

As of today [16 Dec 2020], the country has witnessed 250 916 cases of the coronavirus infection, while 239 416 people have recovered from the disease. Meanwhile, 1743 COVID-19 fatalities have been confirmed.

