Over the last week, 6042 and 4774 COVID-19 cases were reported from Nepal and Sri Lanka, respectively, around 2000 lower in Nepal, but around 200 higher in Sri Lanka compared with corresponding records of the previous week, suggesting a declining trend in Nepal while a slightly increasing trend in Sri Lanka. The number of new reported cases is sharply declining in Bangladesh as the daily case-positivity has dropped below 10% at the end of the week. However, the number of daily deaths remained above 25, and the total number of deaths has recently crossed the mark of 7000. The daily new cases in Pakistan seemed to be stable or in a slightly declining trend after a temporal surge of new cases signaling a new wave. However, there are reportedly certain locations in Sindh province such as the central district of Karachi where the newly laboratory-confirmed cases are seemingly still increasing. The total number of COVID-19 cases in India is approaching to cross the grim mark of 10 million, but the good news is that the daily laboratory-confirmed cases are continuing to fall significantly. Over the week, India's daily new case count was below the mark of 30 000, grossly around 5000 less compared with the previous week.

