[In the past 24 hours, the USA (189 650), Brazil (49 243), and (28 209) have reported the highest numbers of cases. A global total of 10 697 deaths were reported in the past 24 hours (18-19 Dec 2020).

Countries reporting more than 10 000 newly confirmed cases in the past 24 hours (14 countries) include the USA, Brazil, Russia, UK (27 052), India (26 834), Turkey (22 195), Germany (23 970), France (15 565), Italy (16 308), Colombia (13 990), Mexico (12 248), Netherlands (12 217), Ukraine (11 742), and Poland (11 267). A total of 55 countries reported more than 1000 cases in the past 24 hours; 26 of the 55 countries reporting more than 1000 newly confirmed cases are from the European region, 11 are from the Americas region, 9 are from the Eastern Mediterranean region, 4 are from the South East Asia region, 4 are from the Western Pacific region, and one from the African region. A weekend drop in reporting is observed.

Comparing the 7-day averages of daily confirmed cases from the past 7 days and those from 8-14 days ago, case counts have decreased by 14.0%, while daily reported deaths have increased by 4.1%.

Impression: The global daily reported cases continue to increase, with over 600 000 newly confirmed infections in the past 24 hours. Countries in the European and the Americas regions are still showing the largest increases in daily new case counts, followed by the Eastern Mediterranean, South East Asia, and Western Pacific regions. - Mod.UBA]
